<br>
  I like druids.  Druid heals keep a CH rotation working like clockwork.  They can transport guildmates to where they want to go.  They can contribute to the buffing side of the raid, and they can nuke pretty well:  not as lethal as a wizzie, but hey.<br>
<br>
  Comparing a druid to a monk for soloing is, well, a mistake.  Monks have an absolutely insane ability to solo.  It's ludicrous, ESPECIALLY after VI upped our damage tables.  I said at the time it'd make us overpowered in that respect, and I still hold to that today.  A druid is largely dependant on mana to kill things, which inflicts a downtime on them like any caster class.  Monks, on the other hand, are limited by their HP... and they can compensate for that far easier than any caster with a fungi tunic.<br>
<br>
  You're paying the price for playing a class that is a generalist.  You can't expect to be the top class for everything, or hell anything, if you're consistiently in the top 3 for just about everything.<br>
<br>
Laoke<br>
